title: WIAA girls volleyball: Jaden Ward’s fifth-set kill keeps Wisconsin Dells alive
text:
WIAA girls volleyball: Jaden Ward’s fifth-set kill keeps Wisconsin Dells alive State Journal staff 0 
With a little help from Jaden Ward and Tessa Nelson on Thursday night, Wisconsin Dells girls volleyball coach Cyndy Collins was able to extend her coaching career. 
Nelson delivered an assist that Ward knocked home for the decisive point as top-ranked Wisconsin Dells held off visiting Viroqua 17-25, 25-14, 25-16, 21-25, 15-10 in a WIAA Division 2 regional semifinal. 
Collins will finish a 33-year stretch as Wisconsin Dells’ coach after the season , will work the sideline as the Chiefs (30-3) play host to Reedsburg in a regional final at 7 p.m. Saturday . 
Ward totaled 29 kills, Edith Nelson had 13 kills and Tessa Nelson added 32 assists for Wisconsin Dells. Mackenzie Hoffland had 34 assists for Viroqua. 
Reedsburg 3, Portage 0 
Anna Pawlisch had 13 kills to lead the host Beavers over the Warriors 25-14, 25-11, 25-19. 
Kate Gesteland had 29 assists for Reedsburg. Caitlyn Hibner led Portage with eight kills. 
Madison Edgewood 3, Watertown Luther Prep 0 
Hannah Schwenn had a match-high 37 assists and added 13 digs as the Crusaders swept the visiting Phoenix 25-21, 25-15, 25-13. Kendra Lee added 14 kills for Edgewood. 
Brianna Minnema had 11 kills , Lauren Hirsch recorded 14 kills and Jewel St. Germaine added 22 assists for Luther Prep (25-9). 
Edgerton 3, Delavan-Darien 1 
Kellan Schmidt had 19 kills and Kathleen Reilly added 31 assists as the host Crimson Tide defeated the Comets 16-25, 25-23, 25-20, 25-23. Ashlynn Oren recorded 23 digs and two aces for Edgerton (30-10), and Bethany Oren had six blocks. 
McFarland 3, Evansville 0 
Kara Moore had 20 assists to lead the host Spartans (29-12) to a 25-22, 25-22, 25-19 victory over the Blue Devils (19-12). Becka Cronin had 13 kills, two aces and 21 digs for Evansville. 
Platteville 3, Richland Center 0 
Maddie Carroll had 11 kills and Rachel Emendorfer had 18 assists as the host Hillmen (32-4) got a 25-23, 25-14, 25-17 win over the Hornets (19-16). 
Jenna Phillips added 17 assists and five digs for Plattevile and Morgan Stecklein recorded three aces. Madison Rizner had six kills and Keiyah Jonas had 11 assists for the Hornets. 
River Valley 3, Dodgeville 0 
Alyssa Mueller had 17 kills to lead the host Blackhawks (37-5) to a 27-25, 25-21, 25-19 victory over the Dodgers (18-12). 
Katie Valeria had 10 kills, seven blocks and three aces for Dodgeville. Taylor Briehl provided 32 assists for River Valley. 
DIVISION 1 Waunakee sectional 
Madison La Follette 3, DeForest 2 
Megan Corcoran had 20 kills to lead the Lancers (12-25) to a 25-23, 25-17, 14-25, 22-25, 15-10 victory over the host Norskies (25-15). 
Gwen Orr had 13 kills and 11 assists for DeForest. Kayla Daggett had 29 assists for La Follette. 
Middleton 3, Baraboo 0 
Logan Welti recorded 17 kills and 11 digs to lead the host Cardinals (23-17) over the Thunderbirds (10-15) 25-16, 25-16, 25-19. 
Morgan Roberts contributed 11 digs and five aces to help Middleton. 
Monona Grove 3, La Crosse Central 0 
Maddy Braun had 26 assists and eight digs as the host Silver Eagles swept the Red Raiders 25-10, 25-18, 25-12. Kylie Meinholz recorded 11 kills and Sarah Schuster had five blocks for Monona Grove (28-11). 
Emily Haiyden had six kills and Grace Van Dudin added 10 assists for La Crosse Central in the match. 
Waunakee 3, Madison East 0 
Laurel Bailey’s nine kills led the host Warriors to a 25-10, 25-15, 25-10 victory over the Purgolders. 
Tomah 3, Madison Memorial 1 
Jamie Gaarder had 19 kills and 11 digs as the visiting Timberwolves beat the Spartans 25-21, 19-25, 25-18, 25-23. 
Georgia State recruit Sydney Stroud had 18 kills and Jen Roth tallied 19 assists for Madison Memorial. Stroud added 16 digs. 
Holmen 3, Madison West 0 
The host Vikings totaled 16 service aces, led by Kate Balder with five, to sweep the Regents 25-12, 25-8, 25-18. Kara Epping had five kills and 10 digs for West. Lake Geneva sectional 
Stoughton 3, Kenosha Indian Trail 1 
Rachel Hedman recorded 20 kills as the host Vikings (7-7) knocked out the Hawks 19-25, 25-22, 25-17, 25-18. Olivia Panthofer contributed 25 digs for Stoughton. 
Janesville Craig 3, Wilmot 0 
Mel Tinker had 19 assists to lead the host Cougars over the Panthers, 25-12, 25-9, 25-16. Amanda Carlson added five kills and five blocks for Craig. 
Milton 3, Lake Geneva Badger 0 
Senior Rachel Butterfield had 11 kills and Kate Quade added 20 assists as the host Red Hawks swept the Badgers, 25-21, 25-7, 25-10. 
Quade, a senior, added five aces. Maddie Scalissi recorded 22 digs for Milton. 
DIVISION 3 Sheboygan sectional 
Lakeside Lutheran 3, Random Lake 0 
Patience Letko contributed 11 kills as the host Warriors (35-6) swept the Rams 25-13, 25-21, 25-21. Kendal Denson added 21 digs for Lakeside. Brodhead sectional 
Wisconsin Heights 3, Fennimore 0 
Viktoriya Kalsow had 21 assists and 13 digs to lead the host Vanguards over the Golden Eagles 25-15, 25-12, 25-10. Both Kristen Barman and Mackenzie Doherty earned eight kills for Wisconsin Heights. 
Cuba City 3, New Glarus 0 
The Cubans (28-6) stormed to a 25-15, 25-15, 25-12 sweep of the visiting Glarner Knights (12-16). 
Maddie Macht recorded 13 kills and Vanessa Narveson had 18 digs for New Glarus. 
Mineral Point 3, Brodhead 1 
After falling behind in the first set, Clara Chambers had 15 kills to lead the Pointers over the host Cardinals 14-25, 25-18, 25-23, 25-16. Kylie Moe had 16 kills and 22 assists for Brodhead. 
Waterloo 3, Horicon 0 
Madeline Mosher had 17 kills and Claire Mosher had 31 assists as the host Pirates (29-11) swept the Marshmen 25-11, 25-14, 25-10. 
Roseanne Crave led Waterloo with four aces and nine digs. Olivia Pratt had two blocks for the Pirates. 
Deerfield 3, Cambridge 1 
Senior Alexis Eilenfeldt had 23 assists and two aces in the Demons’ 25-20, 28-26, 21-25, 25-12 victory over the visiting Blue Jays. 
Abby Spaanem had 10 kills and three aces for Cambridge. 
DIVISION 4 
Southwestern 3, Pecatonica 0 
The Wildcats (22-1) swept the visiting Vikings (13-11) 25-8, 25-12, 25-9. 
Liz Tisch had three kills and five assists for Pecatonica and Sam Mabin had six digs. Beaver Dam sectional 
Fall River 3, Johnson Creek 0 
Morgan Raley recorded 13 kills, 11 assists and seven blocks as the host Pirates sweep the Bluejays, 25-12, 25-17, 25-12. Mariah Koch led the way in assists for the Pirates with 18 while Alyssa Klecker added four aces in the match. Kelly Tramburg had 13 digs for Fall River. You might also like
